            "answer_text": "Which city in Greece is the oldest? The oldest urban settlement in Greece is Poliochni in Lemnos. See:Poliohni | Greece Attractions and Archaeological sites POLIOCHNI (Prehistoric settlement) LEMNOS (LIMNOS) - GTP. It was founded around 3500 BCE, and predates the nearby Troy by 1000 years! If you are curious to learn about this forgotten city, this is a detailed description:Giota Detsi's answer to Are there any little known civilizations that were surprisingly advanced?  Ruins of Poliochni (photo from Wikipedia) Poliochni is abandoned nowadays. The oldest Greek city surviving till our times is Argos in Peloponnese which was founded around 3000 BCE. For details see: Argos - Wikipedia  The ancient theatre of Argos (photo from Wikipedia) More cities like Athens, Pylos, Sparta, Thebes are almost as old as Argos though. ",
